post_text: Back to school may look different this year, but we would still like to celebrate the end of summer with you! Corvian Booster Club is hosting their annual Back to School Spirit Day at Abbott’s on Thursday, September 17. 20% of the proceeds, from 12pm-9pm, will go to your Booster Club. Abbott’s is adhering to social distancing rules inside and outside. They also have curbside and a pickup window. Don’t forget to mention that you are with Corvian. Hope to see you there! 🍦🍦🍦#corviancommunityschool #corvianathletics #abbottsfrozencustard

post_text:
In this uncertain time, there is certainty in coming together as a community. Corvian did just that last Friday. We had 14 people donate blood. Each blood donation can save up to three lives. This means 42 patients could benefit from the life saving efforts of blood donors at Corvian Community School. We are thankful and grateful to those that came to our school to help. The generosity, compassion, and selflessness of our community is what is needed in our world right now. Visit oneblood.org to learn more about donating the gift of life. ❤️
#corviancommunityschool #corviancares #myoneblood

post_text:
In trying times and unprecedented circumstances, we adjust and make the best of hard situations. So, the Corvian Cardinals 5k is going VIRTUAL! Leading up to our virtual event happening Saturday, March 21, we invite you to join in through

Mind, Body and Spirit…Cardinal Spirit, that is!

As you participate, like and tag Corvian Cardinals 5K and Corvian Community School.
Be sure to use hashtags #corviancardinals5k #allinforcorvian #forthewellnessofall #wearecorviancardinals

We appreciate all who registered for the race. And, we invite ALL community members to take part in this special event highlighting our community’s resilience and support of Corvian Community School. Simply for participating, prizes will be awarded randomly! Check your messages Sunday to see if you’ve won!

*In an effort to support physical distancing yet still show community solidarity, participants posting photos in groups larger than immediate families will be disqualified.

As you participate, like and tag Corvian Cardinals 5K and Corvian Community School.
Be sure to use hashtags #corviancardinals5k #allinforcorvian #forthewellnessofall #wearecorviancardinals

We appreciate all who registered for the race. And, we invite ALL community members to take part in this special event highlighting our community’s resilience and support of Corvian Community School. Simply for participating, prizes will be awarded randomly! Check your messages Sunday to see if you’ve won!

*In an effort to support physical distancing yet still show community solidarity, participants posting photos in groups larger than immediate families will be disqualified.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Due to the progression of the Coronavirus, all Corvian campuses will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th for 2 weeks. We will continue to assess the situation as it develops and determine our date for reopening as needed based on the progression of the virus.

As of now, Corvian will not incorporate our e-learning plan. These 2 weeks will give Corvian teachers and staff a chance to pause and prepare in the event we need to activate e-learning. At this time, Spring Break will not be affected, however we may adjust accordingly should our closure need to be extended. The remainder of the year is a fluid situation until we know how our area will be impacted.

For those who have scheduled meetings, the organizing staff member will reach out directly to you.

We recognize this is a difficult time for everyone, and we appreciate your patience. Please continue communication and confidentially report any Coronavirus cases that directly impact our school community to me at stacey.haskell@corvian.org.

My very best,
Stacey #corviancommunityschool
